==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|be-||be-|lang=ang}}, from {{proto|Germanic|bi-|be-|lang=en}}, from {{proto|Germanic|bi|near, by|lang=en}}. Cognate with {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|be-||be-|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|be-||be-|lang=de}}. More at {{l|en|by}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/bɪ/|/bi/}}, {{SAMPA|/bI/|/bi/}}

===Prefix===
{{en-prefix}}

# {{rare|or|no longer productive}} [[by|By]], [[near]], [[next to]], [[around]], [[close to]]. 
#: {{term|bestand}}, {{term|beset}}
# {{rare|or|no longer productive}} [[around|Around]]; [[about]].
#: {{term|belay}}, {{term|besit}}, {{term|bestir}}, {{term|belive}}, {{term|bewrap}}
# {{rare|or|no longer productive}} [[about|About]], [[regarding]], [[concerning]], [[over]].
#: {{term|bewrite}}, {{term|betalk}}, {{term|betell}}, {{term|bemoan}}, {{term|bemourn}}, {{term|bewail}}, {{term|beknow}}, {{term|besing}}
# {{no longer productive}} [[on|On]], [[upon]], [[at]], [[to]], in [[contact]] with something.
#: {{term|beclothe}}, {{term|becall}}, {{term|besee}}, {{term|behold}}, {{term|befall}}, {{term|bedo}}
# {{no longer productive}} [[off|Off]], [[away]], [[over]], [[across]] 
#: {{term|betake}}, {{term|bego}}, {{term|behead}}
# {{no longer productive}} As an [[intensifier]]; i.e. [[thoroughly]], [[excessively]]; [[completely]].
#: {{term|belabour}}, {{term|behate}}, {{term|bedazzle}}
# {{no longer productive}} All [[around]]; [[about]]; [[abundantly]]; [[all over]].
#: {{term|belave}}, {{term|belick}}, {{term|bescatter}}, {{term|bekiss}}
# {{rare|or|no longer productive}} Forming [[verb]]s derived from [[nouns]] or [[adjectives]], usually with the sense of ''"to make'', ''become'', or ''cause to be"''.
#: ''[[becalm]]'', {{term|bedark}}, {{term|befriend}}, ''[[bedim]]'', {{term|beken}}, {{term|benight}}, {{term|benothing}}, ''[[bewet]]'', ''[[besmooth]]''
# {{archaic|or|informal}} {{non-gloss definition|Used to intensify adjectives meaning "[[adorned]] with something" often those with the suffix {{term|-ed}}}}.
#:''[[besequined]]'', ''[[befeathered]]'', ''[[beclawed]]'', ''[[bewebbed]]'', ''[[betasseled]]''

====Usage notes====
*In its sole remaining productive sense it is readily understood by readers (rarely, listeners) because it adds little meaning to the adjectives it precedes, themselves often nouns besuffixed with -ed.

